  <bioghist id="aspace_7e6bb149fd9156529ff80ad58c9ff6c3">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Company was founded in 1825 by Robert Bacon to make hats. John H. Bacon and Charles N. Bacon later joined the company. Twenty-five years later it began manufacturing all-wool sheet felt for the wallpaper trade, marble polishing and other mechanical uses. It also made felt wheels for polishing and burnishing. The company was bought by Stanley &amp; Samuel McNeily in 1941.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_45a6eae34ecadae5ba0677497dcf24f3">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>Contains incoming correspondence, 1869-1870, 1873, concerning both business and family matters. Also includes a newspaper clipping from the Winchester Star, Oct. 25, 1979, giving a history of the company.</p>  </scopecontent>
